<section class="l-container l-container--9">
    <h2>Admission to our Independent Adoption program is limited to those who meet the following guidelines:</h2>
    <ul class="bullet-list">
        <li>Prefer expectant mother to live in the State of Texas (other areas served Arkansas, Florida, and Oklahoma)</li>
        <li>Adoptive Parents have an approved home study from a licensed agency</li>
        <li>Adoptive Parents married for a minimum of one year</li>
        <li>One adoptive parent must be a U.S. citizen</li>
    </ul>
    <h2>Our Independent Adoption Program Offers:</h2>
    <ul class="bullet-list">
        <li>Guidance from experienced staff</li>
        <li>Client counseling services</li>
        <li>Experienced and respected legal staff</li>
        <li>Specialized parenting education</li>
        <li>Post-adoption support services</li>
        <li>Coordination of a mutually acceptable post adoption contact agreement</li>
        <li>Confidentiality when applicable, unless both parties agree to more openness throughout the process</li>
    </ul>
    <p>To learn more about the Independent Adoption program and the adoption services fee, please email <a class="inline-link" href="mailto:">Ashley Whiteside</a> or call her at 817.922.6000.</p>
</section>





